<p>Madagascar’s army-backed leadership said Colonel Michael Randrianirina will be sworn in as transitional president on Friday after the military took control and parliament voted to impeach President Andry Rajoelina amid weeks of youth-led demonstrations over hardship and governance failures [scmp.com#1][theguardian.com#1][france24.com#1]. The African Union suspended Madagascar from all AU activities, citing its stance against unconstitutional changes of government [aljazeera.com#1][euronews.com#1][scmp.com#1]. Randrianirina, commander of the elite CAPSAT unit, has pledged an 18–24 month transition leading to elections [france24.com#1][dw.com#1][euronews.com#1]. The High Constitutional Court has confirmed him as interim head of state following the impeachment move and Rajoelina’s departure from the country amid unrest [france24.com#1][theguardian.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/gkji6RT2i4gZ361EHhewWls2yCC2pj03_a56RMB4xBlPfq-ET_qhxZ8HvBXcHosKBMm2_dqQcV34JnBQUo1I46ffNjSgc2AGeH2CdAeaM3SH6G0x7TAu2hYDgPuJ-8_d1-fpuVdzuZWJaPeAhoMsSqhkXYrXOmrsZ-iDniFQsA' alt='Protesters gather in Madagascar as political tensions reshape the leadership.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Impeachment move: Lawmakers proceeded with an impeachment vote after Rajoelina’s dissolution decree from exile was defied, deepening a legitimacy crisis [france24.com#1].</li><li>AU dialogue: Randrianirina signaled he is open to talks with the African Union following the suspension [straitstimes.com#1].</li><li>Youth grievances: Protests led by groups calling themselves “Gen Z Madagascar” focused on poverty, corruption, limited access to education, and chronic power and water shortages [france24.com#1][dw.com#1].</li><li>2009 echo: The same CAPSAT unit played a key role in the 2009 military-backed takeover that brought Rajoelina to prominence [france24.com#1].</li><li>Rise and fall: Rajoelina, who once harnessed youth discontent to gain power, was ultimately ousted amid a new wave of youth-driven protests [abcnews.go.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>African Union: The AU suspended Madagascar from all AU activities until constitutional order is restored, condemning the military seizure of power. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/15/au-suspends-madagascar-as-military-leader-to-be-sworn-in-as-president'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li><li>Transitional leadership (Randrianirina): Randrianirina pledged to steer an 18–24 month transition culminating in elections. (<a href='https://www.dw.com/en/madagascar-military-leader-to-become-transitional-president/a-74375773'>DW</a>)</li><li>Rajoelina’s camp: A senior advisor to Rajoelina denounced the military takeover as a coup and disputed claims of unity with youth protesters. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251016-gen-z-revolution-or-coup-against-democracy-madagascar-s-political-upheaval-harkens-back-to-2009'>France 24</a>)</li><li>Youth protesters: Young demonstrators pressed for change over poverty, corruption, education access, and utilities shortages as reasons for mobilization. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251016-gen-z-revolution-or-coup-against-democracy-madagascar-s-political-upheaval-harkens-back-to-2009'>France 24</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/madagascars-military-leader-to-be-sworn-in-as-president-after-coup-african-union-suspends-country-13942466.html'>Madagascar’s military leader to be sworn in as president after coup; African Union suspends country</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251016-gen-z-revolution-or-coup-against-democracy-madagascar-s-political-upheaval-harkens-back-to-2009'>Gen Z revolution or coup against democracy? Madagascar&#x27;s political upheaval harkens back to 2009</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/africa/article/3329214/au-suspends-madagascar-military-prepares-install-colonel-president'>AU suspends Madagascar as 